(5) This Woman Will Decide Which Babies Are Born [ https://substack.com/red=
irect/c3822436-82c5-4a97-bd01-03fcef1a6c92?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Jason Kehe for Wired
Noor Siddiqui founded Orchid so people could =E2=80=9Chave healthy babies.=
=E2=80=9D Now she=E2=80=99s using the company=E2=80=99s gene technology on =
herself=E2=80=94and talking about it for the first time.
Scary title. Great story.
Wired covered Noor Siddiqui and her fertility startup Orchid [ https://subs=
tack.com/redirect/f98583f0-510e-40ef-90bc-db446135e7e9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qi=
fQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. Orchid offers genetic tes=
ting services to prospective parents. Its goal is to provide information ab=
out the genetic risks associated with various diseases and conditions that =
could affect the parents=E2=80=99 future children. The company=E2=80=99s ap=
proach involves analyzing the genetic information of embryos created throug=
h in vitro fertilization (IVF) to assess their risk for over 1,200 diseases=
 and conditions, which goes well beyond the traditional slate of preimplant=
ation screenings. Interestingly, Noor herself is currently using* her compa=
ny=E2=80=99s products (*I will refrain from saying dogfooding in this conte=
xt because it feels weird.)
Obviously, Orchid raises some eyebrows. A cynic might look at Orchid and th=
ink =E2=80=9Cdesigner babies=E2=80=9D or some other worse term. The company=
 does give its customers a fair amount of influencer over the outcomes of t=
he children. But if you are to believe Noor, Orchid is less about producing=
 the =E2=80=9Cperfect child=E2=80=9D and more about reducing suffering. Or =
at least, being aware of that potential for suffering and making an informe=
d choice.
Can technologies be abused? Of course. And it=E2=80=99s up to us a society =
=E2=80=94 social norms, regulations, laws =E2=80=94 to make sure that such =
powerful technologies aren=E2=80=99t abused and we don=E2=80=99t homogenize=
 into a singular designer baby monoculture. That=E2=80=99s a given! But at =
the same time, what is ethical about having a technology that can prevent t=
he proliferation of terrible genetic diseases and not using it? I don=E2=80=
=99t know about you man =E2=80=94 healthier babies sounds pretty damn good =
to me!
Bonus: Problem choice and decision trees in science and engineering [ https=
://substack.com/redirect/d2ede116-c5c5-4ce5-9b0b-d045cff7bb33?j=3DeyJ1IjoiO=
XAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Michael Fischbach in Cell=20
Packy here. If you=E2=80=99re reading these Weekly Doses every week and get=
ting all fired up to go solve some really big, hard problems, take a few mi=
nutes this weekend to read Michael Fischbach=E2=80=99s piece on how to deci=
de which problems to work on, and then take longer than you think you shoul=
d to make that decision. That=E2=80=99s the first of many lessons from the =
paper [ https://substack.com/redirect/66757684-1bbf-4096-b62b-21fb4994d185?=
j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]: spend=
 more time on the problem choice.
I love this paper for a few reasons. First, Elliot [ https://substack.com/r=
edirect/e0c2a49b-f926-48eb-8579-3d2d2cec9f64?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7=
GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] works with Fischbach at Stanford and=
 we=E2=80=99re buddies on Strava. Second, this is the strategy versus execu=
tion idea [ https://substack.com/redirect/2e83c408-273c-4aa6-943c-d2b327c50=
275?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], a=
pplied at the individual level. If you=E2=80=99re reading this, you=E2=80=
=99re a smart, curious person. What you do with your talents matters. Take =
the time to make sure you=E2=80=99re working on the right thing.=20
We=E2=80=99ll be back in your inbox on Tuesday. If you have some time this =
weekend, check out Tegus [ https://substack.com/redirect/72f203a5-2095-432a=
-9e0b-40354569f9b1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-=
6m8ExkRNpU ].
Thanks for reading,
Packy + Dan

